I kindly request the court to consider my potential for rehabilitation at this stage of my life. I want to assure you that I have learned from this experience and am dedicated to making positive changes. I firmly believe that with the guidance given to me, I can become a more responsible individual and contribute positively to society.

In conclusion, I genuinely accept my guilt for the offense of speeding and fully understand and accept the consequences. I sincerely apologize for endangering the safety of others and any inconveniences caused to the court. I vow to work towards personal growth and strive to avoid any future occurrences of such misconduct.

Thank you for your time and consideration, Your Honor.
NEW STATEMENT:

1113
Your Honor,

I, Robert Chapman, appear before this court today to accept full responsibility for the offense of reckless driving. I regretfully admit that I succumbed to the temptation of testing the speed capabilities of my new car, resulting in my engagement in dangerous behavior. I acknowledge the danger I posed to others and sincerely apologize for my disregard for their safety.

Additionally, I would like to acknowledge that I failed to notice the Notice of Intended Prosecution (NIP) that was sent to me. Admittedly, I do not often read my mail, and I genuinely did not see the notice. I understand that it is my responsibility to be aware of legal proceedings and respond appropriately. If I had been aware of the notice, I would have promptly addressed the issue.

Regarding my driving record, I am mindful of the fact that I have accumulated penalty points from three previous speeding incidents. These transgressions weigh heavily on my conscience, and I deeply regret the impact they have had on my driving record. Despite these driving offenses, I want to emphasize that I have no other criminal history.

I would like to emphasize that I have been diagnosed with ADHD. While this does not excuse my actions, it offers an explanation as to why I have struggled to maintain a responsible driving record. I am currently seeking treatment and working on strategies to manage my condition more effectively.

Considering the circumstances surrounding this regrettable incident, I stand here today to express genuine remorse and my commitment to personal growth. I understand the significance of rectifying my behavior and becoming a responsible and law-abiding citizen.

I respectfully request the court's consideration of my potential for rehabilitation at this point in my life. I want to assure you that I have learned from this experience and am fully dedicated to making positive changes. With the support and guidance offered by this court, I believe that I can become a more responsible individual and contribute positively to society.

In conclusion, I wholeheartedly accept responsibility for the offense of reckless driving and fully comprehend and accept the consequences. I extend my sincere apologies for endangering the safety of others and any inconvenience caused to the court. I promise to actively pursue personal growth and ensure that future occurrences of such misconduct are avoided.

Thank you for your time and consideration, Your Honor.
