Regarding my driving record, I understand that I have accumulated penalty points as a result of three previous speeding incidents. These past transgressions weigh heavily on my conscience, and I deeply regret the impact they have had on my driving record. I want to emphasize, however, that I have no other criminal history.

I believe it is important to note that I have been diagnosed with ADHD. While this does not excuse my actions, it provides an explanation for the challenges I have faced in maintaining a responsible driving record. I am currently seeking treatment and implementing strategies to better manage my condition.

In reflecting on the circumstances surrounding this unfortunate incident, I stand before this court today to express sincere remorse and a genuine commitment to personal growth. I fully grasp the significance of rectifying my behavior and becoming a responsible and law-abiding citizen.

I respectfully request the court's consideration of my potential for rehabilitation at this stage in my life. I assure you that I have learned from this experience and am fully dedicated to making positive changes. With the guidance and support provided by this court, I believe I can become a more responsible individual and make a positive contribution to society.

To conclude, I wholeheartedly accept responsibility for the offense of reckless driving and understand and accept the consequences that come with it. I extend my sincere apologies for endangering the safety of others and any inconvenience caused to the court. I pledge to actively pursue personal growth and ensure that future instances of such misconduct are avoided.

